1
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:52,500
[SOUGON]
Script.

2
00:00:52,583 --> 00:00:54,333
A means of communication

3
00:00:54,416 --> 00:00:58,916
for sharing thought,
relaying raw information.

4
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:05,916
[SOUGON] Of all the
world's writing systems,

5
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,916
one is utterly unique. Special.

6
00:01:13,791 --> 00:01:15,625
[SOUGON]
Kanji.

7
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:23,000
[SOUGON]
Verbalize.

8
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,083
[SOUGON] Unlike hiragana
or the Arabic alphabet,

9
00:01:41,166 --> 00:01:45,416
kanji conveys two
things in and of itself.

10
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:49,625
Sound and meaning.
Utterance, significance.

11
00:01:49,708 --> 00:01:51,458
Its relationship to these gives

12
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:54,750
the ancient script
enormous hidden power.

13
00:01:56,083 --> 00:01:59,208
[SOUGON] Concrete thing
or abstract image.

14
00:01:59,291 --> 00:02:00,541
The human mind cannot help

15
00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:03,708
but substitute the
word for the reality.

16
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:07,458
If the word for something
were to be destroyed.

17
00:02:07,541 --> 00:02:11,375
The very concept it
represents would disappear.

18
00:02:11,458 --> 00:02:13,500
Reality would shift.

19
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:18,208
Modern civilization would
fall to ruin on the instant.

20
00:02:32,583 --> 00:02:33,791
[SOUGON]
In times past,

21
00:02:33,875 --> 00:02:36,916
humanity was at one
with the world of truth,

22
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,166
but the written word,
for all we prospered from it,

23
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:42,583
wrought incalculable suffering.

24
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:19,250
[SHOKO] Come on!
You're the manager do something!

25
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,500
[SUZUKI] What are you
waiting for? Call Kokone!

26
00:04:21,583 --> 00:04:23,125
[TANAKA] Without the
Verbalism Reading Corner,

27
00:04:23,208 --> 00:04:24,833
Shirobaco is just a café.

28
00:04:24,916 --> 00:04:27,750
[OURA]
Ugh. Is Hayato still not here?

29
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,166
[SHOKO sighs]

30
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:31,500
[SAKURAKO] This isn't looking
good where is everybody?

31
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:35,291
Cut me some slack,
people you should be here.

32
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:38,125
We should've kicked
things off ten minutes ago.

33
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:42,125
[ITOU]
I see the hype isn't unfounded.

34
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:44,208
The ladies do adore you.

35
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:45,875
I don't know about that, sir.

36
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:49,041
Says "Hayato Kujyo of
the Piercing Good Looks."

37
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:50,458
[HATANO] You ought'a
see the pile of fanmail

38
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:52,375
he rakes in every month.

39
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:53,541
I'm the Diet member,

40
00:04:53,625 --> 00:04:55,333
and all they care
about is my secretary.

41
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:57,708
S'enough to give
a guy a complex.

42
00:04:57,791 --> 00:05:01,458
[ITOU] Now, now. None of us does
our civic duty for the fame.

43
00:05:03,458 --> 00:05:05,166
[TSUTOMU] Seriously.
Fate brought us together.

44
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:08,500
